    <h2>Essential vs Nice-to-Have Equipment</h2>
    <p>When starting a bakery, it's tempting to buy everything on the list. Resist the urge. Start with the essentials and add equipment as your business grows.</p>
    <p><strong>Must-have from day one:</strong> Oven, mixer, refrigerator, baking trays, digital scale, work table</p>
    <p><strong>Add in year 1:</strong> Display counter, additional oven, spiral mixer (if baking bread), dough sheeter</p>
    <p><strong>Add as you scale:</strong> Blast chiller, walk-in cold room, bread slicer, rotary rack oven</p>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What equipment is needed to start a bakery in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The minimum equipment to start a small commercial bakery in India: an oven (convection or deck), a mixer (planetary), a commercial refrigerator, baking trays, a digital scale, and a work table. Budget ₹2,50,000 – ₹5,00,000 for a basic setup. Read our detailed setup guide: <a href="/blog/bakery-setup-cost-india">Bakery Setup Cost in India 2026</a>.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How much does bakery equipment cost in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Bakery equipment costs in India vary widely. A basic home bakery setup costs ₹30,000 – ₹75,000. A small commercial bakery setup costs ₹3,00,000 – ₹8,00,000. A medium commercial bakery costs ₹8,00,000 – ₹20,00,000. A large industrial bakery costs ₹25,00,000 – ₹60,00,000 or more.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do I need both a convection oven and a deck oven? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">It depends on your menu. If you only bake pastries, cakes, cookies, and Indian items like rusks and pav, a convection oven alone is sufficient. If you bake artisan breads, sourdough, baguettes, or anything needing bottom heat and steam, you need a deck oven. Many successful bakeries in India have both — a deck oven for bread and a convection oven for pastries.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the most important piece of equipment in a bakery? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The oven is the most critical piece of equipment in any bakery — it defines your capacity, the quality of your baked goods, and your energy costs. Buy the best oven you can afford. Skimping on the oven will limit your bakery's potential from day one. Read our complete guide: <a href="/blog/bakery-oven-price-india">Bakery Oven Price in India 2026</a>.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Should I buy new or used bakery equipment to start? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A practical approach: buy a new oven (critical equipment — don't compromise on reliability) and consider used equipment for refrigerators, work tables, shelving, and smaller tools. Saving 40–50% on non-critical equipment leaves budget for a better oven. Read our guide: <a href="/blog/new-vs-used-bakery-equipment">New vs Used Bakery Equipment: Honest Pros and Cons</a>.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

